<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Server-Side GTM Integration</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
      Multi-touch attribution for any website — no backend code needed.
      Works with Webflow, WordPress, Squarespace, and any site with Google Tag Manager.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <!-- SECTION: SDK vs sGTM — which is right for you? -->
  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">SDK vs sGTM — Which Is Right for You?</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
      mbuzz has two ways to connect: server-side SDKs and server-side GTM. They do the same thing
      (send attribution data to mbuzz) but suit different teams.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5 mb-6">
      <!-- SDK approach -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Server-Side SDKs</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Ruby, Node.js, Python, PHP, Shopify</p>

        <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Quick to set up — <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">npm install</code>, add middleware, done</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">No third-party infrastructure to manage</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">No monthly hosting costs beyond your own server</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Requires backend access and a developer to install</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Not available for no-code platforms (Webflow, Squarespace)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Changes to tracking require code deploys</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg px-3 py-2">
          <strong>Best for:</strong> Teams with developers who want the simplest, most reliable setup.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- sGTM approach -->
      <div class="border-2 border-indigo-200 rounded-xl p-6 bg-indigo-50/30">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 12h14M5 12a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2v4a2 2 0 01-2 2M5 12a2 2 0 00-2 2v4a2 2 0 002 2h14a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2" /></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Server-Side GTM</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">This page. Works with any website.</p>

        <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">No backend code needed — works with any website</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Non-technical team members can manage tags after setup</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Tracking changes via GTM UI — no code deploys</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Initial setup is painful — DNS, domain config, GTM containers (2-4 hours)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">Monthly hosting cost ($20-90/month depending on provider)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" /></svg>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700">More moving parts — two GTM containers, a hosting provider, DNS records</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-xs text-indigo-700 bg-indigo-100 rounded-lg px-3 py-2">
          <strong>Best for:</strong> No-code sites, agencies, and teams where marketers need to manage tracking without developers.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <strong>TL;DR:</strong> If you have a developer and backend access, the
      <a href="<%= docs_path('getting-started') %>" class="text-indigo-600 underline font-medium">SDKs</a>
      are faster to set up and simpler to maintain. If you don't have backend access or want marketers
      to manage tracking independently, sGTM is worth the setup pain. Both give you the same attribution data.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <!-- SECTION: What is sGTM? -->
  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What is Server-Side GTM?</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Normally, Google Tag Manager runs in your visitor's browser. Every tracking tag (GA4, Facebook, etc.)
      fires from the browser — where ad blockers can block it and Safari can expire your cookies after 7 days.
    </p>

    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8">
      <strong>Server-side GTM</strong> moves that processing to a server <em>you</em> control. Your website
      sends one request to your server, and your server fans it out to all your analytics tools. Because the
      server runs on <em>your domain</em>, cookies are first-party and ad blockers can't touch them.
    </p>

    <!-- Visual: Client-side vs Server-side -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
      <!-- Client-side (the old way) -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12" />
          </svg>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-700">Client-Side (the old way)</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-32 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">Visitor's Browser</div>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
            <div class="w-32 bg-gray-200 text-gray-600 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">GA4 (blocked)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-32"></div>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
            <div class="w-32 bg-gray-200 text-gray-600 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">Facebook (blocked)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-32"></div>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
            <div class="w-32 bg-gray-200 text-gray-600 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">mbuzz (blocked)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 text-xs text-red-600">
          Ad blockers block third-party requests. Safari expires cookies in 7 days. You lose 30-40% of data.
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Server-side (the sGTM way) -->
      <div class="border-2 border-indigo-200 rounded-lg p-6 bg-indigo-50">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
          </svg>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-700">Server-Side GTM (the right way)</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-32 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">Visitor's Browser</div>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
            <div class="w-32 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">Web GTM</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="w-32"></div>
            <div class="w-4 flex-shrink-0"></div>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
                <div class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">GA4 (direct)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
                <div class="bg-indigo-200 text-indigo-800 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center">Your sGTM Server</div>
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg>
                <div class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-2 rounded text-center font-bold">mbuzz</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 text-xs text-green-700">
          GA4 keeps working exactly as-is. A parallel tag sends a copy to your sGTM server, which forwards to mbuzz.
          First-party domain means ad blockers can't block it and cookies last 2 years.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <!-- SECTION: Why you need a custom domain -->
  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Why You Need a Custom Domain</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
      This is the single most important thing to understand about sGTM: <strong>your server must run on your domain</strong>.
      Without it, you lose most of the benefits.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-gray-600 font-medium"></th>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-gray-600 font-medium">Without custom domain</th>
            <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-gray-600 font-medium">With custom domain</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-gray-800">Your server URL</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-500"><code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">abc123.run.app</code></td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-gray-700"><code class="bg-green-50 px-1 rounded text-xs">sgtm.yoursite.com</code></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-gray-800">Cookie type</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-red-600">Third-party</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-green-700">First-party</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-gray-800">Cookie lifespan (Safari)</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-red-600">7 days</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-green-700">2 years</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-gray-800">Ad blocker bypass</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-red-600">No</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-green-700">Yes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 font-medium text-gray-800">Attribution accuracy</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-red-600 font-medium">Poor — visitors who take longer than 7 days to convert are lost</td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 text-green-700 font-medium">Full — visitors tracked across their entire journey</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-indigo-800">
      <strong>Bottom line:</strong> If your sGTM server doesn't run on your domain, Safari users (30-50% of web traffic)
      lose their visitor identity every 7 days. For B2B or considered purchases where buyers take weeks to convert,
      you'll miss most of the journey. The custom domain setup takes a few hours but it's the whole reason sGTM is worth doing.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <!-- SECTION: The 3 pieces you need -->
  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What You Need (3 Things)</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Setting up sGTM with mbuzz requires three pieces. Here's what each one is and how they connect.</p>

    <!-- Visual: The 3 pieces diagram -->
    <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-stretch gap-4">
        <!-- Piece 1: Client GTM -->
        <div class="flex-1 border-2 border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-5 bg-blue-50 relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-4 bg-blue-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded">1</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2 mt-1">Client-Side GTM</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 mb-3">A small JavaScript snippet on your website. Sends page views and events to your sGTM server.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-blue-600 bg-blue-100 rounded px-2 py-1 inline-block">
            You probably already have this
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center md:flex-col">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 rotate-90 md:rotate-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3" />
          </svg>
        </div>

        <!-- Piece 2: sGTM hosting -->
        <div class="flex-1 border-2 border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-5 bg-purple-50 relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-4 bg-purple-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded">2</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-2 mt-1">sGTM Server</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-800 mb-3">A server that receives data from your client GTM and runs tags server-side. Lives on your domain (e.g. <code class="bg-purple-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">gtm.yoursite.com</code>).</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-purple-600 bg-purple-100 rounded px-2 py-1 inline-block">
            Stape.io from $20/mo
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Arrow -->
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center md:flex-col">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-400 rotate-90 md:rotate-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3" />
          </svg>
        </div>

        <!-- Piece 3: mbuzz tag -->
        <div class="flex-1 border-2 border-green-200 rounded-lg p-5 bg-green-50 relative">
          <div class="absolute -top-3 left-4 bg-green-600 text-white text-xs font-bold px-2 py-0.5 rounded">3</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2 mt-1">mbuzz Tag Template</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-green-800 mb-3">A tag that runs inside your sGTM server. Sends visitor, session, and conversion data to mbuzz for attribution.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-green-600 bg-green-100 rounded px-2 py-1 inline-block">
            Import in 2 clicks
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bottom: data flow summary -->
      <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-gray-200">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          <strong>Data flow:</strong>
          Visitor loads your page
          <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">&rarr;</span>
          Web GTM fires two tags: GA4 direct + sGTM forward
          <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">&rarr;</span>
          sGTM tag sends to mbuzz API
          <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">&rarr;</span>
          Attribution calculated
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-amber-800">
      <strong>Already have sGTM?</strong> Skip to <a href="#step-3" class="underline font-medium">Step 3: Add the mbuzz tag</a>.
      Most agencies already have sGTM running — you just need to add the mbuzz tag template.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <!-- SECTION: Step-by-step setup -->
  <!-- ============================================================ -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Setup Guide</h2>

    <!-- Time estimate -->
    <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
        </svg>
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 font-medium mb-1">How long does this take?</p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
            <li><strong>Already have sGTM running?</strong> Adding mbuzz takes ~15 minutes. <a href="#step-3" class="text-indigo-600 underline">Skip to Step 3</a>.</li>
            <li><strong>Setting up sGTM from scratch?</strong> Allow 2-4 hours. Most of that is DNS/domain configuration,
              which can take up to 72 hours for verification depending on your provider. This is a one-time setup.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ========== Step 1: Get sGTM hosting ========== -->
    <div id="step-1" class="mb-12 scroll-mt-24">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 bg-purple-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg">1</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Get an sGTM server running on your domain</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="pl-14">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">
          You need a server to run your tags, and it must live on <strong>your domain</strong> (like
          <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-sm">sgtm.yoursite.com</code>) for first-party cookies to work.
          There are a few ways to set this up.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mb-6">
          This is the most time-consuming step. The server itself spins up fast, but connecting your custom domain
          involves DNS changes that can take anywhere from 30 minutes to 72 hours to verify.
        </p>

        <!-- Provider tabs -->
        <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-6"
             data-controller="toggle"
             data-toggle-default-value="stape"
