            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-800 mb-3">Production setup (custom domain via load balancer):</p>
            <ol class="space-y-3 mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">1</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Create a server container in GTM</strong> (Admin &rarr; Create Container &rarr; Server). Use "Manually provision" and copy the Container Config string.</p>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">2</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Deploy to Cloud Run.</strong> Follow <a href="https://developers.google.com/tag-platform/tag-manager/server-side/cloud-run-setup-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-600 underline">Google's Cloud Run setup guide</a>. Deploy at least 3 instances for production reliability.</p>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">3</span>
                <div>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Set up a custom domain</strong> — this requires an Application Load Balancer in GCP:</p>
                  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2 space-y-1 pl-1">
                    <li>Create a Serverless Network Endpoint Group (NEG) pointing to your Cloud Run service</li>
                    <li>Create a Backend Service using that NEG</li>
                    <li>Create a URL Map (routing rules)</li>
                    <li>Create a Google-managed SSL certificate for your subdomain</li>
                    <li>Create an HTTPS frontend linking the cert and URL map</li>
                    <li>Add a DNS <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">A</code> record pointing your subdomain to the load balancer IP</li>
                    <li>Wait for SSL provisioning (minutes to hours after DNS propagation)</li>
                  </ol>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold">4</span>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Disable default request logging</strong> in Cloud Run settings to avoid the ~$100/month logging bill.</p>
